Galician

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From análise +‎ -izar.

Verb

[edit]

analizar (first-person singular present analizo, first-person singular preterite analicei, past participle analizado)
analizar (first-person singular present analizo, first-person singular preterite analizei, past participle analizado, reintegrationist norm)

  1. (transitive) to analyze (to subject to analysis)

Spanish

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From análisis +‎ -izar.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /analiˈθaɾ/ [a.na.liˈθaɾ] (Spain)
  • IPA(key): /analiˈsaɾ/ [a.na.liˈsaɾ] (Latin America, Philippines)
  • Rhymes: -aɾ
  • Syllabification: a‧na‧li‧zar

Verb

[edit]

analizar (first-person singular present analizo, first-person singular preterite analicé, past participle analizado)

  1. (transitive) to analyze (to subject to analysis)
